content.text: Alienated numbers cannot be expressed in any known mathematical language through: - Algebraic formulas (e.g., x² − 2 = 0) - Trigonometric expressions (e.g., sin(x), cos(x), etc.) - Number sequences or limits - Symbolic function notations ℓ∅ is not the solution to any equation — neither in a finite number of steps nor via generalized infinite limits
